N2  - Hyperandrogenic anovulation refers to the constellation of disorders that present in women with irregular menses, hirsutism and/or acne across the lifespan. Understanding the clinical signs and symptoms of each diagnosis in the differential and laboratory testing to confirm or exclude a diagnosis allows a clinician to appropriately counsel and treat the patient. Copyright Published by Elsevier Inc.
